lilbub;photo;https://www.instagram.com/p/BnT5mJ-FAXf;https://scontent-amt2-1.cdninstagram.com/vp/d18e6d83ab1d60a9d6aa80688079cd55/5D333521/t51.2885-15/e35/39926274_662218197511063_5364683245289996288_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-amt2-1.cdninstagram.com;1536078568;4-9-2018 18:29;539;49442;This is BUB with our beloved vet Dr Woodruff
column5: who has been our family’s vet for over ten years. He’s been coming to check on BUB every two weeks for over 3 years! We wanted to address something that many of you have been noticing
column6: which is that the left side of BUB’s face is enlarged. We first noticed the growth on her jaw over a year ago
column7: and have been monitoring it very closely since. Since then she’s seen two other specialists and has had three CT scans. I want to let everyone know that so far
column8: this has not affected BUB’s wellbeing whatsoever. It does not cause her any pain
column9: doesn’t affect her voracious appetite or ability to eat
column10: and thanks to some recent therapies (including tons of love and attention) she is feeling the best she’s felt in years. I’ll be posting a video that goes into more detail regarding her jaw growth
column11: but for now I wanted to assure everyone that she is feeling great and as always is getting the best medical attention that a magical space cat could ask far. We appreciate everyone’s concern and support. GOOD JOB BUB! #goodjobbub #bilbobubbins #scienceandmagic #lilbub;30844342;1

That’s really what this is all about: sharing her life and giving people a glimpse of the joys and the challenges of caring for a special needs pet as special as BUB.;;;;

Last week BUB had an accident at home. She underwent a successful surgery; and I am thrilled to report that she is doing great; is as spry as ever; has the appetite of a lion; and seems to have no idea that anything even happened.
